cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper deals with the problem of determining the most important factors in determining the classification outcome of a dataset. This is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the area of classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also employs cooperative game theory to develop an influence measure for each feature in determining the classification outcome. This brings in elements of game theory and mechanism design, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

The paper also analyzes the effects of user profiling on Google's online display advertising, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). 

Finally, the paper uses an axiomatic approach to develop the influence measure, which involves mathematical reasoning and proofs. This could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
